Gunshots were heard before a headteacher, her husband and seven-year-old daughter were found dead at their home, according to reports. A rifle range near Epsom College, where Emma Pattison was head, has been sealed off as detectives continue to investigate.  The bodies of Ms Pattison, 45, her daughter Lettie, seven, and her husband George, 39, were found when officers were called to the private school by the South East Coast Ambulance Service at about 1.10am on Sunday morning. More to follow...